==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bred
<hw>Bred</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <def><pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> of
<er>Breed</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Bred out</b></col>, <cd>degenerated.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧The
strain of man's <xex>bred out</xex> into baboon and monkey.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Shak.</au> -- <col><b>Bred to arms</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Arms</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Well bred</b></col>. <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>Of
a good family; having a good pedigree.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧A gentleman <xex>well
bred</xex> and of good name.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Shak.</au> <mark>[Obs., except
as applied to domestic animals.]</mark> <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>Well brought
up, as shown in having good manners; cultivated; refined;
polite.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

